Responsive image to manage size .img-fluid

ALERTS

use .alert

for colored alerts 
.alert .alert-success
.alert .alert-danger
.alert .alert-primary
.alert .alert-warning
.alert .alert-secondary
.alert .alert-dark
.alert .alert-info

for making links in the alert of same color use .alert-link (for the 'a' tag)

DISMISSABLE OR CLOSING ALERTS !
we make a div with classes alert , alert-success(for color) , alert-dismissible
requires js

    <div class="alert alert-success alert-dismissible fade show">
      <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="alert">&times;</button>
      <strong>Success</strong> alert <a href="#" class="alert-link">Click Here !</a> 
    </div>

for animations we used fade show

BUTTONS IN BOOTSTRAP

use classes btn and for color use 

btn btn-success
btn btn-primary
btn btn-danger
btn btn-warning
btn btn-danger
btn btn-dark and so on...
<button type = "button" class="btn btn-primary"></button>

OUTLINES
 use btn btn-outline-primary

BUTTON SIZES 

btn btn-primary btn-lg (large)
btn btn-primary btn-sm (small)

use .btn-block for full width button

ACTIVE DISABLED 
use .active and .disabled

SPINNERS TO BUTTONS

use .spinner-border , .spinner-border-sm

BUTTON GROUP

.btn-group

for vertical groups 

.btn-group-vertical

DROPDOWNS WITH BUTTONS


classes in button : .btn .btn-primary .dropdown-toggle 
extra attribute : data-toggle="dropdown"

then make a div with class .dropdown-menu

and include 'a' elements with class .dropdown-item


BADGES

These are used to provide extra info about a text 

use span and use class .badge for badge 

and alongside with .badge use
.badge-primary
.badge-secondary
.badge-success
.badge-warning
.badge-danger
.badge-info
.badge-dark

for different colors

Example : <h1>Sample heading <span class="badge badge-info">new</span></h1>

for round badges use .badge-pill

Example : <h1>Sample heading <span class="badge badge-pill badge-info">new</span></h1>

badge inside elements 

<button class="btn btn-info">Message <span class="badge badge-light">5</span></button>


PROGRESS BAR 

add .progress  to the class of containing element and class .progress-bar to child

and inside child element use style and then width property to set the progress bar

Striped progress add .progress-bar-striped

Animated bar : .progress-bar .progress-bar-striped .progress-bar-animated

PAGINATION 

use ul for this 
use .pagination class in ul
use .page-item class in li
use .page-link class in anchor tag in li 
use .active class in li to highlight the respective page link
use .disabled to make link unclickable
use .pagination-lg for larger or pagination-sm for smaller boxes in ul
use .justify-content-center for center alignment and .justify-content-end for right aligned


BREAD CRUMBS 

other type for pagination

use .breadcrumb in ul
use .breadcrumb-item in li

LISTGROUPS

use .list-group in ul 
use .list-group-item in li
use .active for active state

Linked List Group

use .list-group-item in a tag and .list-group-item-action for hover

use .diabled for unclickable links

use .list-group-flush for removing borders

use .list-group-item-info etc for colors 


BOOTSTRAP CARDS

.card class in containing element 
.card-body for content
.card-header for header
.card-footer for footer
.card-title to add card title to headings
.card-text in p tag for text 
.card-link for card links
.card-img-top or card-img-bottom for images
.card-img-overlay for making text written over the image
.card-columns for grid like arramgements of card (pinterest example)
.card-deck for grid card layout of equal height and width
.card-group :: same as card-deeck with left and right margins


BOOTSTRAP DROPDOWNS

use .dropdown in containing div and .dropleft or .dropright or .dropup for dropdown position
use .dropdown-toggle and data-toggle="dropdown" in the button
use .dropdown-menu to actually build the dropdown
use .dropdown-item to actually add elements

use .dropdown-divider class to separate link with horizontal line
use .dropdown-header for adding heading to the items
use .active .disabled for active or disabled dropdown items
use .dropdown-item-text for adding simple text


COLLAPSIBLE 

use data-toggle="collapse" and data-target="#id" attribute in the button
use .collapse in the div containing data and also give id to it.

by default data is hidden, in the div containing content we can use .show class to make it appear initially.

Use the data-parent attribute (in div having content) to make sure that all collapsible elements under the specified parent will be closed when one of the collapsible item is shown.


NAVS

for simple nav menu
add .nav to a ul and .nav-item to li
use .justify-content-center or .justify-content-end for center and right alignment

use .nav-tabs to turn liks into tabs
use .nav-pills to display as pills it like tabs but coloured whereas tabs are like borders
justify tabs/pills using .nav-justified for equal length


DYNAMIC TABS

1. Nav tabs 
in anchor use tab data-toggle="tab" href="#id"
2. Tab panes
use .tabcontent in containing element
use .tab-pane .containier and also give id


BOOTSTRAP NAVBAR

use .navbar in nav element 
use .navbar-expand-lg|sm|md|xl in nav element for changing horizontal to vertival layout (responsive)
use bg-info etc in nav for color
use .navbar-brand for logos n logo images in nav bar (before ul after nav)

Collapsable navbar

To create a collapsible navigation bar, use a button with class="navbar-toggler", data-toggle="collapse" and data-target="#thetarget". Then wrap the navbar content (links, etc) inside a div element with class="collapse navbar-collapse", followed by an id that matches the data-target of the button: "thetarget".

(above 4 lines of text from w3schools.com)

inside the div are the usual ul and li tags

Dropdown navbar 
see how to make a dropdown and implement it here also . its the similar process

Form in navbar

for form with search and a button 

at first we use form-inline class in the form element (to keep button and search bar together)

in input we use .form-control (styling) mr-sm-2 (margin btw button)

For including anything with search bar 
we use .input-group-prepend or .input-group-append
First create a div with class .input-group
then we created text inside span with class .input-group-text .input-group-prepend
then created input element

use .fixed-top to fix navbar on top
use .fix-bottom to fix the navbar on the bottom
use .sticky-top to make it stick to top when scrolled down














































































































































































































